}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== "G1700814100200 V2.0 REV:B" and a date code of '''2209''' is silkscreened on one RT514C's board. :There is no obvious indicator RT514C is the '''PRO-NETS''' model of this device. :However, it's on the label affixed to the device.. not with any indicator that it is the model name, but [http://www.geeks.com/details.asp?invtid=RT514C-PB it seems to be]. :All caps on the board are '''JACKCON''' branded.
It would appear to be running '''eCos'''.
==Included PSU(s)== The power supply included with the device (in at least US regions) :looks to be a '''Channel Well Technology''' CAP012121.
